<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-09-28T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-09-28T12:00:00-05:00" n="817" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d817">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.252/63a: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Culbertson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-09-28T12:00:00-05:00">September 28,
                                1931—noon</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>45. Your 119, September 25, 6 p.m. Approved, although the Department
                            would prefer 30 days notice of termination instead of 15. Accept the
                            latter if unable to obtain the 30 days, which is the usual period in
                            agreements of this kind.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>